KnowledgeBase.Title: Example Vector compareNE 006
KnowledgeBase.RelatedFunctions: compare compareEQ compareLE compareGE compareLT compareGT

Example.Description: These examples use the compareNE function to compare two Vectors and return the Boolean value, true or false. The corresponding keys and values of each Vector are compared to determine whether one Vector is equal to the other.

Syntax.Note: The value of the first Vector is not equal to the value of the second Vector.
The value of the first Vector is not equal to the value of the second Vector.
